  "prompt": "Has anyone really \"died laughing\"?",
  "response": "The expression \"died laughing\" is usually used figuratively to mean that someone found something extremely funny. However, in very rare cases, there have been reports of people dying due to laughter. Such incidents typically involve underlying medical conditions. \n\nFor instance, uncontrollable laughter can lead to cardiac arrest, asphyxiation, or a burst aneurysm. One documented case is that of a Danish audiologist named Ole Bentzen, who, in 1989, reportedly laughed so hard at a scene in the movie \"A Fish Called Wanda\" that his heart rate increased to a critical level, resulting in a fatal heart attack.\n\nWhile these incidents are extremely rare, they highlight how certain medical conditions can be exacerbated by extreme emotional responses, including laughter. In healthy individuals, laughing is generally considered beneficial to health, reducing stress and promoting well-being.",
